description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF continued to ramp up its supply operations to support the country’s efforts to respond to the COVID-19 pandemic as well as to continue programmes and respond to other emergencies. By December, the Office had implemented and achieved its Supply Plan. ;Sustainable supply solutions were developed through emergency preparedness, prepositioning and warehousing strategies, including fostering local market capacities. UNICEF provided procurement services, technical support and guidance on procurement and supply chain management to partners and government counterparts in order to provide timely support for the delivery of programmes the women and children of Sierra Leone. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
